Reasoning: The paper introduces a framework for supporting learning to program in the paradigm of Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a declarative logic programming formalism. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Software Engineering (cs.SE). The focus on teaching and giving hints to students also suggests that the paper could be more pedagogical in nature, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to the cs.PL or cs.SE sub-categories.
